\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Archetype}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 An archetype is a prototype or model from which something is based.  The character archetypes listed here derive from Joseph Campbell's }{\f4\fs24\b0\i1 The Hero with a Thousand Faces}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 , and  are deeply rooted in the myths and legends of many cultures.  A significant character's role can often be associated with one of these archetypes.}
