\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx-720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Hero}\cell 
\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx-720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The essence of the  hero is not bravery or nobility, but self-sacrifice.  The mythic hero is one who will endure separation and hardship for the sake of his clan.  The hero must pay a price to obtain his goal.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The hero's journey during a story is a path from the ego, the self, to a new identity which has grown to include the experiences of the story.  This path often consists of a separation from family or group to a new, unfamiliar and challenging world (even if it's his own back yard), and finally a return to the ordinary, but now expanded, world.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The hero must learn in order to grow.  Often the heart of a story is not the obstacles he faces, but the new wisdom he acquires, from a mentor, a lover, or even from the villain.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Other characters besides the protagonist can have heroic qualities.  This can be especially true of the antagonist.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Heroes can be willing and adventurous, or reluctant.   They may be group and family oriented, or loners.  They may change and grow themselves, or act as catalysts for others to grow and act heroic.  The hero can be an innocent, a wanderer, a martyr, a warrior, a vengeful destroyer, a ruler, or a fool.  But the essence of the hero is the sacrifice he makes to achieve his goal.}\cell{
