\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx-720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Threshold}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Guardian}\cell 
\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx-720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The threshold guardian is the first obstacle to the hero in his journey.  The threshold is the gateway to the new world the hero must enter to change and grow. }
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The threshold guardian is usually not the story's antagonist.  Only after this initial test has been surpassed will the hero face the true contest and the arch-villain.   Frequently the threshold guardian is a henchman or employee of the antagonist.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 But the threshold guardian can also be an otherwise neutral character, or even a potential ally\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2  such as the police lieutenant who warns the hero private detective off the case, or the Cowardly Lion who first frightens and then joins Dorothy on her journey to Oz.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1\f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The role of the threshold guardian is to test the hero's mettle and worthiness to begin the story's journey, and to show that the journey will not be easy.  The hero will encounter the guardian early in the story, usually right after he starts his quest.}\cell{
